%S A139629 1,2,6,17
%N A139629 Row sums of A139624, number of connected directed multigraphs with loops and no vertex of degree 0, with n arcs, which are transitive (the existence of a path between two points implies the existence of an arc between those two points).
%C A139629 Bojicic et al define 1, 2, 6, 17, 51, 151, 453, 1354, 4062, 12172, 36516, 109506,.. as a Hankel transform, probably only a coincidental overlap. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 16 2026
%H A139629 R. R. Bojicic, Marko D. Petkovic, P. M. Rajkovic, P. Barry, <a href="https://doi.org/10.2298/FIIL2514807B">On the Hankel transform of the number of closed walks on regular trees</a>, Filomat 39 (14) (2025), 4870-4819, d=3 in g(x) in section 4.
%Y A139629 Cf. A139628, A139630.
